results.name: A005282(n) - A011185(n-1).
comment: A005282 is the sequence of smallest numbers such that the pairwise sums of not necessarily distinct elements are all distinct, whereas A011185 is the sequence of smallest numbers such that the pairwise sums of distinct elements are all distinct.
Sequence has negative terms; the first one is a(65) = -130.
link: Klaus Brockhaus, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2400
